items.abstract:
<jats:p><p><strong>Abstract.</strong> Assemblages of Middle Devonian (Givetian) phytoplankton from the Holy Cross Mountains include sphaeromorphs possessing blister-like ornamentation typical of the genus <i>Tapajonites</i> Sommer &amp;amp; van Boekel, 1963. Study of the sculptural elements under high magnification indicates the presence of patterns resembling impressions of pyrite crystals. It is suggested that ornamentation in <i>Tapajonites,</i> or at least in some sphaeromorphs assignable to that genus, is of a secondary nature.</p>
                    </jats:p>
title: Note on the preservational nature of ornamentation in sphaeromorphs assignable to <i>Tapajonites</i> Sommer &amp; van Boekel, 1963 (Prasinophyta?)
